cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.IR, cs.AI, cs.CV 

This paper deals with natural language processing (NLP) and machine learning techniques for modeling words. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also uses Hierarchical Dirichlet Process, which is a probabilistic model, indicating that it could belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also deals with topic modeling, which is a subfield of information retrieval (cs.IR) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the paper uses word embeddings, which are commonly used in computer vision (cs.CV) as well.
